ulture</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Geography_and_places" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Geography</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Health_and_fitness" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Health</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#History_and_events" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">History</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Mathematics_and_logic" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Mathematics</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Natural_and_physical_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Nature</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#People_and_self" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">People</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Philosophy_and_thinking" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Philosophy</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Religion_and_belief_systems" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Religion</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Society_and_social_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Society</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Technology_and_applied_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Technology</a></dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n<div style="float:right; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #1D368A;background: #1D368A;color: white;padding: .1em;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 100%;margin-bottom: 0px;border-bottom: none;-moz-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; -webkit-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0;"><span class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size: 80%;padding-right: 0.5em;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Sega/Intro&amp;action=edit"><font color="white">edit</font></a>&#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em;"><span class="mw-headline" id="The_Sega_Portal"><font color="white"><big><br />\n<a href="/wiki/File:SEGA_logo.svg" class="image"><img alt="SEGA logo.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/SEGA_logo.svg/300px-SEGA_logo.svg.png" width="300" height="100" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/SEGA_logo.svg/450px-SEGA_logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/SEGA_logo.svg/600px-SEGA_logo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="300" data-file-height="100" /></a><br />\nThe Sega Portal</big></font></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block; border: 1px solid #1D368A; vertical-align: top; background: #f3f3ff; color: black; margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 1em; margin-top: 0em; padding-top: .3em;-moz-border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em; -webkit-border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em; border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em;">\n<div style="position:relative;top:-3em"><span id="P:S"></span><span id="P:SE"></span></div>\n<div class="shortcutbox plainlist noprint" role="note" style="float:right;border:1px solid #aaa;background:#fff;margin:.3em .3em .3em 1em;padding:.4em .6em;text-align:center;font-size:smaller;line-height:2em;font-weight:bold"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut" title="Wikipedia:Shortcut">Shortcuts</a>:\n<ul>\n<li><span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=P:S&amp;redirect=no">P:S</a></span></li>\n<li><span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=P:SE&amp;redirect=no">P:SE</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p><b>Sega Corporation</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">\xe6\xa0\xaa\xe5\xbc\x8f\xe4\xbc\x9a\xe7\xa4\xbe\xe3\x82\xbb\xe3\x82\xac</span><span style="display:none">,</span> <i><a href="/wiki/Kabushiki_gaisha" title="Kabushiki gaisha">Kabushiki gaisha</a> Sega</i>)</span>, pronounced <b>s\xc3\xa6\'\xc9\xa1\xc9\x99</b> (US/Canada/UK) or <b>si\'\xc9\xa1\xc9\x99</b> (Australia/New Zealand) usually styled as <b>SEGA</b>, is a <a href="/wiki/Multinational_corporation" title="Multinational corporation">multinational</a> video game software developer and an <a href="/wiki/Arcade_games" class="mw-redirect" title="Arcade games">arcade software</a> and <a href="/wiki/Arcade_cabinet" title="Arcade cabinet">hardware</a> development company headquartered in <a href="/wiki/%C5%8Cta,_Tokyo" title="\xc5\x8cta, Tokyo">\xc5\x8cta</a>, <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a>, with various offices around the world. Sega previously developed and manufactured its own brand of <a href="/wiki/Video_game_console" title="Video game console">home video game consoles</a> from 1983 to 2001, but a restructure was announced on January 31, 2001 that ceased continued production of its existing home console, effectively exiting the company from the home console business. While arcade development would continue unchanged, the restructure shifted the focus of the company\'s home video game software development to consoles developed by various third-party manufacturers.</p>\n<p>Sega\'s head offices, as well as the main office of its domestic division, <b>Sega Corporation</b> (Spartata), are located in \xc5\x8cta, Tokyo, Japan. Sega\'s European division, <b>Sega Europe Ltd.</b>, is headquartered in the <a href="/wiki/Brentford" title="Brentford">Brentford</a> area of London in the United Kingdom. Sega\'s North American division, <b>Sega of America Inc.</b>, is headquartered in San Francisco; having moved there from <a href="/wiki/Redwood_City,_California" title="Redwood City, California">Redwood City, California</a> in 1999. <b>Sega Australia</b> is headquartered in Sydney, and <b>Sega Publishing Korea</b> is headquartered in <a href="/wiki/Jongno" title="Jongno">Jongno</a>, <a href="/wiki/Seoul" title="Seoul">Seoul</a>, <a href="/wiki/Korea" title="Korea">Korea</a>.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Video_games" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Video games"><img alt="WPVG icon 2016.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e0/WPVG_icon_2016.svg/20px-WPVG_icon_2016.svg.png" width="20" height="20" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e0/WPVG_icon_2016.svg/30px-WPVG_icon_2016.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e0/WPVG_icon_2016.svg/40px-WPVG_icon_2016.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="249" data-file-height="249" /></a> <b><a href="/wiki/Sega" title="Sega">More about Sega</a> ...</b></div>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align:center;"><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Sega&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page"><b>Show new selections</b></span></a></span></div>\n<div class="portal-column-left-wide">\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #1D368A;background: #1D368A;color: white;padding: .1em;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 100%;margin-bottom: 0px;border-bottom: none;-moz-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; -webkit-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0;"><span class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size: 80%;padding-right: 0.5em;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Sega/Selected_article/2&amp;action=edit"><font color="white">edit</font></a>&#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article"><font color="white"><i>Selected article</i></font></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block; border: 1px solid #1D368A; vertical-align: top; background: #f3f3ff; color: black; margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 1em; margin-top: 0em; padding-top: .3em;-moz-border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em; -webkit-border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em; border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em;">\n<p><i><b>Crazy Taxi</b></i> is a series of <a href="/wiki/Video_game" title="Video game">video games</a>, developed by <a href="/wiki/Sega_Hitmaker" title="Sega Hitmaker">Hitmaker</a> and published by <a href="/wiki/Sega" title="Sega">Sega</a>, first released to <a href="/wiki/Video_arcade" class="mw-redirect" title="Video arcade">arcades</a> in 1999. The success of the <a href="/wiki/Arcade_game" title="Arcade game">arcade version</a> prompted Sega to release the game on their <a href="/wiki/Dreamcast" title="Dreamcast">Dreamcast</a> console in 2000. It was the <a href="/wiki/List_of_best-selling_video_games#Dreamcast" title="List of best-selling video games">fourth best-selling game</a> on that system, selling over a million copies. The game was later ported to the <a href="/wiki/PlayStation_2" title="PlayStation 2">PlayStation 2</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nintendo_GameCube" class="mw-redirect" title="Nintendo GameCube">Nintendo GameCube</a> and <a href="/wiki/IBM_PC_compatible" title="IBM PC compatible">PC</a> with sequels also appearing on <a href="/wiki/Xbox" title="Xbox">Xbox</a> and <a href="/wiki/Game_Boy_Advance" title="Game Boy Advance">Game Boy Advance</a> systems.</p>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Sega/Selected_article" title="Portal:Sega/Selected article">...Archive</a></b> \xe2\x80\xa2 <b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Sega/Selected_article/Nominations" title="Portal:Sega/Selected article/Nominations">Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;"><b><a href="/wiki/Crazy_Taxi_(series)" title="Crazy Taxi (series)">Read more...</a></b></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #1D368A;background: #1D368A;color: white;padding: .1em;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 100%;margin-bottom: 0px;border-bottom: none;-moz-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; -webkit-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0;"><span class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size: 80%;padding-right: 0.5em;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Sega/Did_you_know&amp;action=edit"><font color="white">edit</font></a>&#160;</span>\n<h2 style="font-size:100%;font-weight:bold;border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know..."><font color="white"><i>Did you know...</i></font></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="display: block; border: 1px solid #1D368A; vertical-align: top; background: #f3f3ff; color: black; margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 1em; margin-top: 0em; padding-top: .3em;-moz-border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em; -webkit-border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em; border-radius: 0 0 1.5em 1.5em;">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Sega" title="Sega">Sega</a> also owns the entertainment fun center, <b><a href="/wiki/GameWorks" title="GameWorks">GameWorks</a></b>, which was founded in <a href="/wiki/1997" title="1997">1997</a>.</li>\n<li><b><a href="/wiki/Sega" title="Sega">Sega</a></b> was founded in <a href="/wiki/1940" title="1940">1940</a> as Standard Games (later Service Games) in <a href="/wiki/Honolulu,_Hawaii" class="mw-redirect" title="Honolulu, Hawaii">Honolulu, Hawaii</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both;"></div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #1D368A;background: #1D368A;color: white;padding: .1em;text-align: center;font-weight: bold;font-size: 100%;margin-bottom: 0px;border-bottom: none;-moz-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; -webkit-border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 0; border-radius: 1.5em 1.5em 0 